d":"dcc6daea-456e-4328-8cff-f9c6da6d2891","position":{"commit_sha":"bc7dc2961a322d47afbc646119d0c8b3107f3600","position":"1784742735446238001-dcc6daea-456e-4328-8cff-f9c6da6d2891"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-217_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"007b200a-5427-4a88-a88c-815e2a8f9d31","comments":[{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Epic run complete for the 5 originally-decomposed leaves: 1aa8 (verify outcome tallying), 35d2 (DCO sign-off identity-neutral guidance), 6777 (ChatGPT connector-limited agent guide), fe4c (--force gate-bypass clarification), b24d (plan-review hierarchy-incomplete fix, TDD held-out oracle: 12 tests authored RED-first, 2 held out from implementer initially then restored, mutation/teeth check confirmed real assertions, full pytest suite green). All 5 changes merged to origin/main individually as each reached LLM-Review+1/Verified+1 (no separate composite submit needed). Epic left OPEN: c2c5-53a7-2ce0-4d98 (verify_findings telemetry wiring) was discovered mid-run and linked as a child but was explicitly scoped OUT of this epic execution per standing session decision -- leaving it open and unworked rather than force-closing the epic past rebar's open-children guard or expanding scope unilaterally.","timestamp":1784742735446238001}],"created_at":1784581489070448001,"creation_channel":"import","deps":[{"link_uuid":"63e52803-80c2-431a-a000-b4ccc61095be","relation":"relates_to","target_id":"55c1-0e70-cd8d-40f5"}],"description":"## Summary\n\nImplement the approved 2026-07-19 Rebar Janitor remediation plan. The work restores optionality by correcting contributor guidance, clarifying the force/invariant contract, making LLM verification resilient without accepting empty outcomes, preventing plan reviews from passing with incomplete hierarchy context, and documenting safe ChatGPT workflows for connector-limited environments.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Contributor and agent guidance uses each contributor's configured real DCO identity; Joe Oakhart's bot identity appears only where an explicitly automated workflow requires it.\n- [ ] Public transition guidance states that force bypasses all gates, including future gates, while ticket-system invariants such as the open-children close prohibition remain non-bypassable.\n- [ ] Verification preserves flexible provider-independent parsing and self-healing, but no semantically empty result can be accepted as a valid review outcome.\n- [ ] Plan review cannot produce an ordinary clean pass when the ticket hierarchy was loaded incompletely, unless the omitted context is demonstrably irrelevant.\n- [ ] ChatGPT-specific guidance explains how to use Rebar safely when the GitHub repository is a read-only mirror and native clone, Gerrit, or tracker access is unavailable.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"AGENTS.md","reason":"Canonical contributor and ChatGPT guidance"},{"path":"CONTRIBUTING.md","reason":"DCO contract"},{"path":".agents/rules/rebar.md","reason":"Derived agent guidance"},{"path":"src/rebar/_lib_writes.py","reason":"Public force semantics"},{"path":"src/rebar/llm/verify_models.py","reason":"Verifier response normalization"},{"path":"src/rebar/llm/plan_review/orchestrator.py","reason":"Hierarchy completeness handling"},{"path":"docs/chatgpt-agent-guide.md","reason":"Connector-limited environment guidance"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["relates_to","55c1-0e70-cd8d-40f5"]],"parent_id":null,"parent_status_uuid":"98cf382c-ce79-4814-bf4f-505e827d1